        <section id="analysis">
            <h2>6. Aligning Fundamental & Technical Analysis</h2>
            <p>Do not treat these as opposing methodologies. Blend them to establish high-probability setups:</p>
            
            <div class="grid-2">
                <div>
                    <h3>1. Fundamental Analysis (The Direction)</h3>
                    <p>Looks at macroeconomic indicators (Central Bank Interest Rates, Inflation Data, CPI prints, and Employment numbers) to determine overall currency strength.</p>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <h3>2. Technical Analysis (The Timing)</h3>
                    <p>Uses historical charts, support or resistance levels, market structure shifts, and candlestick patterns to determine the exact execution price.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="box box-info">
                <h3>💡 The Complete Structural Alignment Process</h3>
                <p><strong>Step 1:</strong> Read an economic calendar. Discover that the Federal Reserve is increasing interest rates (making the US Dollar fundamentally strong).</p>
                <p><strong>Step 2:</strong> Shift to your technical charts. Ignore all sell patterns. Look exclusively for clean Support Levels or Higher Lows to time a high-probability buy entry.</p>
            </div>
        </section>

