        <section id="structure">
            <h2>8. Market Structure Combined with Price Action</h2>
            <p>Market structure maps institutional order flow. Price always shifts across identifiable structural phases:</p>

            <h3>The Three Structural Sequences</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>The Uptrend:</strong> Clean, sequential series of <strong>Higher Highs (HH)</strong> followed by <strong>Higher Lows (HL)</strong>. Only search for buy triggers on retests of a valid Higher Low.</li>
                <li><strong>The Downtrend:</strong> Sequential series of <strong>Lower Lows (LL)</strong> followed by <strong>Lower Highs (LH)</strong>. Only search for sell entries on retests of a valid Lower High.</li>
                <li><strong>The Ranging Phase:</strong> Price action moves flatly inside clear horizontal Support and Resistance floors and ceilings.</li>
            </ul>

            

            <div class="box box-warning">
                <h3>🚨 Execution Trigger: The Break of Structure (BOS)</h3>
                <p>When an active uptrend fails to push to a fresh Higher High, turns downward, and breaks cleanly beneath the most recent structural <strong>Higher Low (HL)</strong>, a <strong>BOS</strong> has occurred. This proves institutional trend direction has officially flipped bearish. Stop buying immediately and look to sell on the next pullback to a Lower High.</p>
            </div>
        </section>

